_people\", \"score\": 0.5722790116153009, \"rank\": 0.74615484571911, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The original Course des Cafes\", \"from\": 1722, \"to\": 1751}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 1757, \"to\": 1762}, {\"ngram\": \"waiters\", \"from\": 1801, \"to\": 1808}, {\"ngram\": \"a 8km course\", \"from\": 1844, \"to\": 1856}, {\"ngram\": \"order\", \"from\": 1861, \"to\": 1866}, {\"ngram\": \"the values\", \"from\": 1877, \"to\": 1887}, {\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 1891, \"to\": 1896}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The dash through central Paris celebrated the dexterous and, yes, by their own admittance, sometimes famously moody men and women without whom France would not be France.\", \"from\": 1935, \"to\": 2105, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1960, \"end\": 1965, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.183375841503011e-19, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2078, \"end\": 2084, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.999998969222892, \"rank\": 5.676301951374686e-07, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 2098, \"end\": 2104, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.999998969222892, \"rank\": 5.676301951374686e-07, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The dash\", \"from\": 1935, \"to\": 1943}, {\"ngram\": \"their own admittance\", \"from\": 2004, \"to\": 2024}, {\"ngram\": \"sometimes famously moody men\", \"from\": 2026, \"to\": 2054}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 2059, \"to\": 2064}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Why?\", \"from\": 2107, \"to\": 2111, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Because they make France's cafes and restaurants tick.\", \"from\": 2112, \"to\": 2166, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2130, \"end\": 2136, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.999998969222892, \"rank\": 5.676301951374686e-07, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"restaurants\", \"from\": 2149, \"to\": 2160}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Without them, where would the French gather to put the world to rights over drinks and food?\", \"from\": 2167, \"to\": 2259, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 2218, \"to\": 2227}, {\"ngram\": \"rights\", \"from\": 2231, \"to\": 2237}, {\"ngram\": \"drinks\", \"from\": 2243, \"to\": 2249}, {\"ngram\": \"food\", \"from\": 2254, \"to\": 2258}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Where would they quarrel and fall in (and out of) love?\", \"from\": 2260, \"to\": 2315, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"out of) love\", \"from\": 2302, \"to\": 2314}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And where else could they simply sit and let their minds wander?\", \"from\": 2316, \"to\": 2380, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"their minds\", \"from\": 2361, \"to\": 2372}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They have penned songs and poems about their \\\"bistrots\\\", so attached are they to their unpretentious watering holes that for generations have nourished their bodies and souls.\", \"from\": 2382, \"to\": 2557, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"songs\", \"from\": 2399, \"to\": 2404}, {\"ngram\": \"poems\", \"from\": 2409, \"to\": 2414}, {\"ngram\": \"their \\\"bistrots\", \"from\": 2421, \"to\": 2436}, {\"ngram\": \"their unpretentious watering\", \"from\": 2463, \"to\": 